In [[Greek mythology]], the name '''Amphinome''' ([[Ancient Greek]]: Ἀμφινόμη) may refer to: * Amphinome, a [[Nereid]].<ref>[[Homer]], ''[[Iliad]]'', 18. 44</ref> * Amphinome, wife of [[Aeson]] and mother to [[Jason]] and [[Promachus]]. She and her husband were persecuted by king [[Pelias]] of [[Iolcus]]. After Pelias had killed her husband and younger son, Amphinome stabbed herself with a sword. As she lay dying she pronounced a curse against the king.<ref>[[Diodorus Siculus]], ''The Library of History'', 4. 50. 2</ref> * Amphinome, one of the daughters of Pelias, given by Jason in marriage to Andraemon, brother of [[Leonteus (mythology)|Leonteus]].<ref>Diodorus Siculus, ''Library of History'', 4. 53. 2</ref> * Amphinome, wife of Arizelus and mother of [[Harpalion]].<ref>[[Quintus Smyrnaeus]], ''Fall of Troy'', 10. 75</ref>
