{{Infobox protected area | name = Channahon State Park | iucn_category = III | photo = Channahon State Park 4.jpg | photo_width = | photo_alt = | photo_caption = Channahon State Park, April 2018 | map = Illinois | map_width = 225 | map_caption = Map of the [[U.S. state]] of [[Illinois]] showing the location of Channahon State Park | location = [[Will County, Illinois|Will County]], [[Illinois]], [[United States|USA]] | nearest_city = [[Channahon, Illinois]] | coordinates = {{coords|41|25|27|N|88|13|39|W|display=inline, title}} | area = {{convert|20.5|acre}} | established = 1932 | visitation_num = | visitation_year = | governing_body = [[Illinois Department of Natural Resources]] }}
'''Channahon State Park''' is an [[List of Illinois state parks|Illinois state park]] in [[Will County, Illinois|Will County]], [[Illinois]], [[United States]]. The park was named after a Native American word meaning "the meeting of the waters". It lies adjacent to the [[confluence]] of the [[DuPage River|Dupage]], [[Des Plaines River|Des Plaines]], and [[Kankakee River]]s.
The park is near the municipality of [[Channahon, Illinois]]. It is served by [[U.S. Highway 6]].
==See also== * The [[Shabbona Trail]] goes through Channahon State Park and ends in [[Gebhard Woods State Park]]. * Gebhard Woods is located along the {{convert|61|mi|adj=on}} long National Park Service [[Illinois and Michigan Canal]] National Heritage Corridor.
