'''Epsilon radiation''' is [[tertiary radiation]] caused by [[secondary radiation]] (''e.g.'', [[delta radiation]]).{{contradict-inline|date=January 2018}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.iupac.org/ACD/V7_karol/E.html#anchor49458|title="EC  Electron capture"|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20050215150322/http://www.iupac.org/ACD/V7_karol/E.html|archive-date=February 15, 2005}}</ref> Epsilon rays are a form of [[particle radiation]] and are composed of [[electron]]s. The term was coined by [[J. J. Thomson]], but is very rarely used today.

