{{short description|A cold-water current flowing south-westward from the Bering Strait, along the Siberian Pacific coast and the Kamchatka Peninsula}}
{{Unreferenced|date=December 2009}}
The '''Kamchatka Current''' is a cold-water current flowing south-westward from the [[Bering Strait]], along the [[Siberia]]n Pacific coast and the [[Kamchatka Peninsula]]. A portion of this current then becomes the [[Oyashio Current]] while the remainder joins the warmer [[North Pacific Current]].

