{{Infobox government agency |agency_name = Ministry of Energy |type = |nativename = {{nq|وزارت توانائی}} |nativename_a = |nativename_r = |logo = |logo_width = |logo_caption = |seal = |seal_width = |seal_caption = |picture = Pakistan_Ministry_of_Energy_Logo.png |picture_width = 250px |picture_caption = |formed ={{Start date|df=yes|2017|8|4}} |preceding1 = |preceding2 = |dissolved = |superseding = |jurisdiction = |headquarters =[[Islamabad]], [[Islamabad Capital Territory]] |coordinates = |employees = |budget = |minister1_name = [[Omar Ayub Khan]] |minister1_pfo = Federal Minister for Energy (Power Division) |Secretary_name = |minister2_pfo = |chief1_name = Irfan Ali |chief2_name = [[Power Secretary of Pakistan]] |agency_type = |parent_agency = |child1_agency = |child2_agency = |keydocument1 = |website = |footnotes = |map = |map_width = |map_caption = }}
The '''Ministry of Energy, Power division''' is a [[Government of Pakistan|Pakistan Government's]] [[:Category:Pakistan federal departments and agencies|federal and executive]] level [[Ministry (government department)|ministry]] created on 4 August 2017 after merging of the [[Ministry of Petroleum and Natural Resources]] with the power division of the [[Ministry of Water and Power]] (now renamed [[Ministry of Water Resources (Pakistan)|Ministry of Water Resources]]), respectively.<ref>{{cite news|title=Pakistan's new PM forms cabinet with an eye to 2018 poll|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-pakistan-politics-idUSKBN1AK09A|accessdate=6 August 2017|work=Reuters|date=2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=DailyTimes {{!}} Cabinet takes oath: Abbasi creates seven new ministries|url=http://dailytimes.com.pk/pakistan/05-Aug-17/cabinet-takes-oath-abbasi-creates-seven-new-ministries|accessdate=6 August 2017|work=dailytimes.com.pk|language=en}}</ref> The ministry has two division - petroleum and power. The Petroleum Division is headed by the [[Petroleum Secretary of Pakistan|Petroleum Secretary]] and the Power Division is headed by the [[Power Secretary of Pakistan|Power Secretary]]. It is currently headed by [[Omar Ayub Khan]] as of 11 September 2018.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Junaidi |first1=Ikram |title=Six federal ministers inducted into cabinet |url=https://www.dawn.com/news/1432416 |accessdate=12 September 2018 |work=DAWN.COM |date=12 September 2018}}</ref>
